This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a technique for speeding up reinforcement learning algorithms. It also involves the use of Q-learning and Actor-Critic algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Robotics (cs.RO) categories as it deals with control problems and simulations. The System and Control (cs.SY) category may also be relevant as it involves control problems. Finally, the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category may be relevant as reinforcement learning is a type of machine learning that is inspired by the way animals learn.
